{"title_page": "Detlef Bothe (actor)", "text_new": "{{short description|German actor}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Detlef Bothe\n| image = \n| caption = \n| birth_name = \n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1965|07|24|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Braunschweig]], [[West Germany]]<ref name=\"filmportal\">{{cite web|title=Detlef Bothe|url=http://www.filmportal.de/person/detlef-bothe_6dcb21f999fc49d5b8a1fed4b3333f96|publisher=filmportal.de|language=German|accessdate=24 October 2015}}</ref>\n| yearsactive = 1990\u2013present\n| occupation = actor, director, producer}}\n\n'''Detlef Bothe''' (born 24 July 1965) is a German [[actor]], [[screenwriter]], [[film director]] and producer.<ref name=\"filmportal\" /> Since the early 1990s, he has appeared in numerous film and television productions, both German and international. In 2015, he appeared in the [[James Bond in film|''James Bond'' film]] [[Spectre (2015 film)|Spectre]] as a henchman, in a scene where he and [[Q (James Bond)|Q]] ([[Ben Whishaw]]) are seen riding a cable car in the Austrian Alps.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mi6-hq.com/sections/articles/bond-24-report-010315-detlef-bothe-interview?t=&s=mi6_update&id=03859|title=Detlef Bothe Speaks|work=MI6-HQ.COM}}</ref>\n\nBothe became a prominent on-screen representative of the Nazi leader [[Reinhard Heydrich]] as he has portrayed Heydrich in two films pertaining to [[Operation Anthropoid|his assassination]]: The 2011 Czech film ''[[Lidice (film)|Lidice]]'', the 2016 British film ''[[Anthropoid (film)|Anthropoid]]'' and in 2005 [[BBC]] documentary series about [[holocaust]] ''Auschwitz: The Nazis and the 'Final Solution'''.<ref name=\"MAZ-Online\">{{cite news|last1=Nowak|first1=Ricarda|title=Ein Mann in fieser Mission|url=http://www.maz-online.de/Nachrichten/Kultur/Ein-Mann-in-fieser-Mission|accessdate=6 March 2018|work=MAZ-Online.de|publisher=M\u00e4rkische Allgemeine Zeitung|date=20 November 2015|language=German}}</ref> Bothe is often praised as \"dead ringer\" ([[twin]]) of Heydrich.<ref name=\"Pirodsky\">{{cite web|last1=Pirodsky|first1=Jason|title=Movie Review: The Butcher of Prague Gets His Due in \u2018The Man with the Iron Heart\u2019 (aka \u2018HHhH\u2019)|url=https://www.praguereporter.com/home/2017/6/8/movie-review-the-butcher-of-prague-gets-his-due-in-the-man-with-the-iron-heart-aka-hhhh|website=The Prague Reporter|accessdate=16 July 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Selected filmography==\n{{Div col}}\n*1993: ''[[Tatort]]'' (TV Series) - Hubert\n*1992: ''Der Knappe des Kreuzes''\n*1995: ''[[Brother of Sleep]]'' - Lukas\n*1996: ''After Hours''\n*1996: ''[[Gegen den Wind]]'' (TV Series) - Eric\n*1997: ''[[14 Days to Life]]'' - Rudi\n*1997: ''Ballermann 6''\n*1998: ''[[Balko]]'' (TV Series) - Richie Schwingbrodt\n*1998: ''Appetite'' - Godfrey\n*1999: ''Sara Amerika'' - Jim J.\n*1999: ''[[Bang Boom Bang]]'' - Arne\n*1999: ''[[After the Truth]]'' - Siebert\n*1999: ''Schmetterlinge der Nacht'' - Killer's Helper\n*2000: ''[[The Calling (2000 film)|The Calling]]'' - Scouser\n*2001: ''Himmlische Helden'' - Flex\n*2001: ''Ein g\u00f6ttlicher Job'' - Orkton\n*2001: ''99euro-films'' - (segment \"Ich schw\u00f6re\") (segment \"Loreley S.\")\n*2001: ''Sass'' - Ede\n*2002: ''Feiertag'' (also writer, director and producer) - Ingo\n*2002: ''Vienna'' - Thomas\n*2002: ''[[Extreme Ops]]'' - Ratko\n*2003: ''Die Musterknaben III'' (TV Movie) - Fliege\n*2003: ''[[Baltic Storm]]'' - Victor Renko\n*2003: ''Gone \u2013 Eine t\u00f6dliche Leidenschaft'' - Mike\n*2004: ''Abgefahren \u2013 Mit Vollgas in die Liebe'' - Matador\n*2004: ''Vinzent'' - Vinzent / Olaf Podesch\n*2004: ''Meine Frau, meine Freunde und ich'' (also writer, director and co-producer) - Richard Wippe\n*2005: ''[[Speer und Er]]'' (TV Mini-Series)\n*2005: ''Rose'' - Steve\n*2006: ''[[Die Rosenheim-Cops]]'' (TV Series) - Konrad Rottmann\n*2006: ''Die Wilden Kerle 3'' - Bodyguard \u00d6\n*2006: ''[[FC Venus]]'' - Louis Doderer\n*2007: ''Neben der Spur'' - Dieter\n*2008: ''Auf der Suche nach dem S